  "text": "HomeStyleShe wore linen workwear while at the Time100 Summit in New York City.Photo: Craig Barritt/Getty Images for TIMEEver since announcing her engagement to Prince Harry, the world's eyes have been fixed on Meghan Markle — and her style. We'll be following the Meghan Markle Effect™ with our column, \"Meghan Markle Wore a Thing.\"Wearing suits in spring weather can be tricky, mainly because most of them are too heavy to be worn in warmer weather. For Meghan Markle, however, no season can best her chic workwear.On Wednesday, the Duchess of Sussex spoke at the Time100 Summit at New York City's Lincoln Center, wearing a tan linen Ralph Lauren suit paired with a crisp white button-down. The quiet luxury-coded outfit consists of the brand's relaxed-fit Russell Twill Blazer featuring subtle power shoulders. Waist down, rather than lean into her penchant for skinny jeans, Markle switched it up by going for matching wide-leg, Twill Pleated trousers. Photo: TheStewartofNY/GC ImagesScroll to ContinueRecommended ArticlesRalph Lauren's brown leather Calfskin Buckle Belt cinched her waist, while pointy Manolo Blahnik suede pumps completed the look. Jewelry-wise, she reached for gold Tabayer hoop earrings, a gold watch and the late Princess Diana's Cartier diamond tennis Bracelet. Prince Harry accompanied Markle, who, for his part, kept it straightforward in a navy suit, white button-down and black dress shoes.See more of our favorite looks from the Duchess of Sussex in the gallery below:Homepage Photo: Jemal Countess/Getty Images for TIMEPlease note: Occasionally, we use affiliate links on our site. This in no way affects our editorial decision-making. (Learn about our sponsored affiliate offerings.) Do you have an emerging brand you want to share with Fashionista readers? Jumpstart your business with our affordable digital offerings.Subscribe to Our Newsletter",
